Method - a block of code that perorms a specific function created within a class.

Syntax:

  accessModifier returnType methodName(parameters) {
  //method body
  }
  
The method name has to be descriptive as it explains what the method does.

Example:
        
        public class MathHelper {
              public static int add(int a, int b) {
               return a + b;
    }
}
        
To Call this method, create and instance of the class MathHelper, and call this method.
The method can also be called without creating an instance of the class it is contained by using
the keyword 'Static' between the access modifier and return type.

Method parameters are values accepted by the method.
